    "Background": {
      "text": "Life threatening neurologic emergency associated with the use of neuroleptic agents\n[1]\n[2]\nCan occur with single dose, increasing dose, or same dose as usual\n[3]\nMost often seen with \"typical\" high potency antipsychotics (\nhaloperidol\n)\nalso occurs with newer \"atypicals\" (\nrisperidone\n,\nolanzapine\n)\nantiemetics (\nmetoclopramide\n,\npromethazine\n)\nwithdrawal of anti-Parkinson medication\nDevelops over 1-3 days\nMajority of deaths occur from complications of muscle rigidity\nMortality rates up to 5 to 20%\n[4]",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
